for 5 minutes.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":300,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":300},{"id":1026385,"guid":"3D15F910F1BB11EAA9FDD72D2A670561","previous_id":null,"previous_guid":null,"modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"06770C72E19242E7B1C894C5BECD5614","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Set up Slot\/Dot blot apparatus"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"9BBDA28D4C634AF4AEFCF282AB1DCE9A","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">1. Assemble 3 sheets of cut GB003 blotting paper pre-wetted with transfer buffer (25 mM Tris, 200 mM Glycine, 20% methanol) to the dot blot apparatus.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">2. Pre-wet a cut sheet of PVDF in 100% methanol for 30 sec and then wash the PDVF in transfer buffer for 2 min.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">3. Lay the PVDF membrane on the GB003 blotting paper and seal the slot\/Dot blot apparatus.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":300,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":300},{"id":1026410,"guid":"8BA24810F1BE11EA9F6E9DFDEB42F693","previous_id":1026384,"previous_guid":"7E820510F1BB11EAA9FDD72D2A670561","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"F7F7F48FE8BE41E1A7E2064AB4C6A7CF","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Incubate with HRP-conjugated antibody, wash and develop"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"9456BB39439C4C01A6039E9866D0F440","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">1. Once the membrane is dry, add it to 10 ml of TBST (20 mM Tris, 150 mM NaCl, 0.1% Triton X-100, pH 7.5) (or PBST) containing HRP-conjuated antibody and incubate with gentle shaking 40 minutes.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">2. Wash the blot 4 times for 5 minutes with 10 ml of TBST<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">3. Add ECL or colorimetric substrate, develop for 2-5 min, and image blot.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">4. Record the results.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":3600,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":3600}],"document":null,"materials":[],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">This is a simple slot\/dot blot protocol for detecting antigen on a membrane.  Using the method outline here, one can achieve results in under 90 min because it eliminates the need for running a gel, transfering the protein in a transfer apparatus, blocking, secondary antibody incubation and the washes between primary and secondary antibodies.<\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1599564108}